    <div class="ma-compare">
      <div class="ma-box">
        <h4>Simple Moving Average (SMA)</h4>
        <p>Adds the last N closing prices and divides by N. Equal weight to all periods. Slower to react — smooths out noise better. Better for longer-term trend identification.</p>
        <span class="ma-tag slow">Lagging • Smooth</span>
      </div>
      <div class="ma-box">
        <h4>Exponential Moving Average (EMA)</h4>
        <p>Applies a multiplier giving more weight to recent candles. Reacts faster to price changes. More signals — but also more false positives. Preferred for shorter-term strategies.</p>
        <span class="ma-tag fast">Reactive • Responsive</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

