  <div class="section" id="glossary">
    <div class="tag-line"><span></span></div>
    <div class="sec-head">
      <h2>Trading Glossary</h2>
      <span class="sec-sub">Key terms used throughout TrendTrooper</span>
    </div>
    <div class="glossary">
      <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">ATR</div><div class="gloss-def">Average True Range. Measures volatility over N periods. Used for dynamic stop placement.</div></div>
      <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">Signal ID</div><div class="gloss-def">Unique identifier attached to each TradingView alert. Used by TrendTrooper for replay protection.</div></div>
      <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">Drawdown</div><div class="gloss-def">The peak-to-trough decline in account value. Controlling drawdown is the #1 rule of longevity.</div></div>
      <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">Webhook</div><div class="gloss-def">HTTP POST request TradingView sends to TrendTrooper when an alert fires. Contains the full signal payload.</div></div>
      <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">Bracket Order</div><div class="gloss-def">An entry with pre-defined stop-loss and take-profit attached. Removes emotion from exits.</div></div>
      <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">VWAP Bias</div><div class="gloss-def">Price above VWAP = bullish intraday sentiment. Below VWAP = bearish. TrendTrooper uses this as a filter.</div></div>
      <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">Paper Mode</div><div class="gloss-def">Simulated trading. Orders execute against real prices but no real money moves. Always test here first.</div></div>
      <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">Confluence</div><div class="gloss-def">Two or more indicators or price levels agreeing. Stronger signals come from confluent setups.</div></div>
      <div class="gloss-item"><div class="gloss-term">R:R Ratio</div><div class="gloss-def">Risk-to-Reward. A 1:2 ratio means risking $100 to make $200. Never take trades below 1:1.5.</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
